                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13489321" author="tmueller" created="Fri, 2 Nov 2012 09:09:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The first part is implemented in revision 1404899&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13502020" author="tmueller" created="Wed, 21 Nov 2012 14:48:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In revision 1408729, after each 100 traversed nodes, a log message with level warning is written: &quot;Traversed &amp;lt;count&amp;gt; nodes with filter &amp;lt;filter and query statement&amp;gt;; consider creating an index or changing the query&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will not detect all slow queries (only those that traverse the repository), but let&apos;s leave it at that for now. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13555114" author="tmueller" created="Wed, 16 Jan 2013 15:28:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are queries that use an index but are still quite slow, because the index is very unspecific (for example an index on a basic node type). Such queries should also be logged.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, logging once per 100 nodes is too much it seems. Logging once per 1000 nodes should be enough.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
